hackathon-description-text: We love coding...and ducks. We hope that through this we can inspire many high schoolers to pursue a computer science education.

hackathon-judges.judge-role: Oros Family Professor and Chair of the Department at UMBC

hackathon-requirements: Make something that could help someone, we are looking for unique ideas and themes that carry throughout the entire program. Its not necessarily the solution itself that matters, but the process the coders took to get to that solution.
hackathon-rules:
1. No bad language or condeming any other group
2. Light competition is healthy but it is not worth more than your friends
3. HAVE FUN

hackathon-prizes.prize-title: DROCON Quadcopter Drone w/ HD Camera
Canbor Virtual Reality Headset w/ Remote

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Come up with unique solutions to problems we face. These problems can be as simple or as complex as possible.
Would someone else use this product? How so?
Does the program fulfill its purpose and does it actually work?

hackathon-description-header: A hackathon for high school students by high school students
